{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"34ee50a1-066f-4bc6-8d5a-1e0c2c5afcc6","content":"Here's what you need to change:\n\n**1. `.csproj` — Remove the assembly reference, add MSTest v3 NuGet package, and bump the test SDK:**\n\n- Remove `Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework` assembly reference\n- Add the `MSTest` v3 metapackage (includes TestFramework, TestAdapter, and Analyzers)\n- Update `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk`\n\n**2. Test code — No changes needed.** MSTest v3 uses the same `Microsoft.VisualStudio.TestTools.UnitTesting` namespace and attributes (`[TestClass]`, `[TestMethod]`, `[Timeout]`, etc.).\n\nWant me to apply these changes to your project?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"2e2253b8-5551-45ff-96b8-2dc69f8b01a0","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to upgrade from the old MSTest (via assembly reference to `Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework`) to MSTest v3.\n\nHere's what needs to change:\n\n1. **Remove the assembly reference** to `Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework`\n2. **Add the MSTest v3 NuGet package** — MSTest v3 uses a single package `MSTest` (version 3.x)\n3. **Update `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk`** to a newer version (or it may no longer be needed with MSTest v3 since MSTest 3.x includes the test SDK via `MSTest.Sdk` or the `MSTest` metapackage)\n\n\n4. **Target framework compatibility** — MSTest v3 supports .NET Framework 4.6.2 and above, so the current target should work fine.\n5. **Namespace** — The using statement stays the same since MSTest v3 maintains the `Microsoft.VisualStudio.TestTools.UnitTesting` namespace.\n\nThe simplest path forward is to just install the `MSTest` NuGet package (version 3.x), which is a meta-package that bundles everything needed including the test framework and adapter.\n\nFor the actual migration, I need to remove the old assembly reference from the project file and replace it with a package reference to MSTest v3, optionally updating the Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk version as well. The `MSTest` metapackage bundles the framework, adapter, and analyzers together, but I'll still need to add `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` separately since it provides the test host infrastructure that MSTest depends on.","outputTokens":972},"id":"da6ac0c1-6ca0-463b-961a-ad2f175994c9","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:58:09.436Z","parentId":"203884aa-49c1-4d71-bef9-b89d943983a2"}
